Rothschild in Talks With Hayward on Investment Fund, Times Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-04-05T07:16:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/rothschild-in-talks-with-hayward-on-investment-fund-times-says.html
U.K. financier  Nathaniel Rothschild 
is in talks with  Tony Hayward , BP Plc’s former chief executive
officer, about setting up an investment fund, the London-based
Times reported.  Hayward, Rothschild and Julian Metherell, currently Goldman
Sachs Group Inc.’s head of U.K. investment banking, are looking
at creating a cash shell that would make acquisitions in the oil
and gas industry, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 